* * * * *
* INTRO *
* * * * *
Apac is a static webserver.

It is be available from
	http://qaa.ath.cx/apac.tgz
or
	http://i860.sf.net/apac.tgz
	        









 END SECTION 
---------------
* * * * * * * *
* DESCRIPTION *
* * * * * * * *
Apac supports a subset of HTTP/1.1
	. if-modified (client side caching)
	. partial content (continuing)
	. See ~ line 84 of defines.h for a full list
	        









 END SECTION 
---------------
* * * * * * * * * * * *
* BUILD INSTRUCTIONS  *
* * * * * * * * * * * *
NON-GNU MAKE (i.e. pmake, BSD make)
 SOLARIS
  make solaris [file flag] makefile.nongnu
  make install
 OTHER
  make [file flag] makefile.nongnu
  make install
GNU MAKE
 ANY
  make
  make install
	        









 END SECTION 
---------------
* * * * * * * * * * * *
* SPACE REQUIREMENTS  *
* * * * * * * * * * * *
[File        ][Approx Size][1]
~/.apac.conf	        200
~/.apac.mime	      1 100
apac		     19 000
---------------------------
Installed system     32 000
For build[2]	    207 000
	        









 END SECTION 
---------------
* * * * *
* NOTES *
* * * * *
[1] In Bytes. Approximate size is an overestimate

[2] This is the amount of space needed for a build
    from source for the build directory
